  "prompt": "What is the meaning of sending nudge in hike messenger?",
  "response": "In the context of Hike Messenger, sending a \"nudge\" is a feature that allows you to grab the attention of someone you\u2019re chatting with. It is similar to a gentle reminder or alert designed to prompt the recipient to respond if they haven't yet or if you want to emphasize your last message. The nudge feature can be useful if the person you're chatting with is not responding for a while, and you want to make sure they see your message. This functionality is comparable to the \"poke\" feature on other platforms, providing a light-hearted way to interact with friends.",
